    <title>Reverberation</title>
    <p>
        PulseEffects uses the reverberation plugin developed by
        <link href="https://calf-studio-gear.org">Calf Studio</link>.
    </p>
    <terms>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Pre Delay</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Additional delay - corresponds to a distance between sound source and the
                nearest wall
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Decay Time</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Time it takes for reverberation to fade out
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Amount</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Amount of processed signal (reverberation) in the output
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Dry</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Amount of unprocessed signal in the output
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Bass Cut</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Removes low frequencies from the reverberation
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Treble Cut</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Removes high frequencies from the reverberation
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Diffusion</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Increase its value for less uniform reverberation
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Room Size</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Size of the space that simulated reverberation occurs in - determines times
                between reflections
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">High Frequency Damping</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Cutoff high reflections high frequencies - causes higher frequencies to decay
                faster
            </p>
        </item>
    </terms>
